  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age ≥ 65

          -  Sinus rhythm, PR &lt; 220ms, QRS &lt; 110ms

          -  Heart failure (NYHA class III-IV or II with hospitalization for heart failure)

          -  Ejection Fraction &gt; 50%, restrictive mitral inflow, Lateral E/e' &gt; 12 or septal E/e' &gt;
             15, Left atrial index volume &gt; 34 ml/m²

          -  Atrial dyssynchrony syndrome: (TTE) inter-atrial time delay ≥ 70ms (difference between
             tricuspid and mitral P-A intervals or between mitral and tricupsid P-A' intervals with
             DTI)

          -  Left atrio-ventricular asynchrony: Time Difference between tricupsid and mitral A wave
             duration ≥ 35ms.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
